description.en: Ontology for modelling tourism-related data, including cities, hotels, restaurants, events, and transport systems.
description.undefined: Ontology for representing key concepts in tourism, including cities, hotels, restaurants, attractions, transport, and events.

abstract.value: The domain of the ontology is framed around the modelling of tourism-related data, including cities, hotels, restaurants, events, and transport systems. The scope of the ontology will be based on the characteristics of these entities and their relationships within the tourism sector.
